<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-042-008 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 445 291</DOCID><JOURNAL>C Users Journal  Oct 1991 v9 n10 p134(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT R andamp; D Publications Inc 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Cray Research upgrades compiling systems. (New Products:industry-related news and announcements) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Cray Research Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Ticker:    CYR.andO;Product:   CF77 5.0 (Compiler) (Product introduction)Cray Standard C Compiler 3.0 (Compiler) (Product introduction)Cray Ada 2.0 (Compiler) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     C Programming LanguageProduct IntroductionCompilersFORTRAN.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Cray Research, Inc. has released upgrades of its three main compilingsystems: the CF77 5.0 FORTRAN Compiling System, the Cray Standard C Compiler3.0, and Cray Ada 2.O.andM;These Cray Research compilers offer a distinct advantage to users becausethey automatically optimize programs.andP;  With their support tools for enhancingperformance, these compilers provide supercomputer users high levels ofperformance and reliability.andP;  In fact, Cray Research's CF77 recently placedfirst in industry tests performed at the Department of Energy's ArgonneNational Laboratory.andP;  And on the Perfect Benchmarks suite (a group of realapplication codes collected and evaluated by the Center for SupercomputingResearch and Development at the University of Illinois) optimizationimprovements to the CF77 FORTRAN computer yielded an average speedup of 13times for all the codes in this test suite, with some codes achievingspeedups of up to 130 times.andP;  And Cray Ada meets US Department of Defensestandards for mission-critical software - a stringent requirement forreliability.andM;The Cray Standard C Compiler also outperforms all other commerciallyavailable vectorizing C compilers.andP;  In contrast to competing products, thenew Cray Standard C Compiler performs optimization and vectorization bydefault, which results in significant speedup without user intervention.andP;  Infact, the compiler is so reliable that UNICOS 6.0, Cray Research's newestrelease of its UNIX-based operating system, is also compiled with fulloptimization.andM;The Cray Standard C Compiler also performs automatic parallel processing,called Autotasking2.andP;  Autotasking2 allows applications to utilize multipleCPUs without programmer intervention.andM;For more information contact Cray Research (612) 683-3538.andO;</TEXT></DOC>